summary: Do you consider Jonah to be a part of the ghc
question: Do you consider Jonah to be a part of the ghc
answer:
I’ve probably explained this better before but oh well. Personally, I don’t. The reason for that being because “The Good Hair Crew” was a lighthearted inside joke that was formed over a much more serious situation. It was a joke that Cyrus made during the situation in which Buffy was being targeted because of her hair (and race), and when she was missing her mom who was deployed. Jonah wasn’t there for that, and I don’t think he would have really understood the depth of it even if he were there at the time.

Obviously I don’t think he’s ~excluded~ from it, either. The four of them are obviously a pretty tight friend group at this point. I just personally think it would be weird to include someone in an inside joke that they were outside of. He’s obviously made jokes about it too. I could see them joking about him being an honorary member, but making sure that there was still a line between him and the actual GHC. Which is why we have GHC+Jonah.

summary: so many people think that one scene in cyrus outside is the b[redacted]h scene but... i honestly don't think so?? we all know...
question: so many people think that one scene in cyrus outside is the b[redacted]h scene but... i honestly don't think so?? we all know what he wears in the finale, and i have a strong feeling that scene occurs at the party, not beforehand. but eh who knows! he definitely was talking to tj tho, you can tell bc of how tall the other person is
answer:
I’m pretty sure that all of the moments we saw in that summer promo were only from the June episodes. There’s a good chance that the clip of Jonah and Amber on a date, and the one of Bex and Bowie looking at what appears to be wedding invitations are from 316. The clips of the GHC+Jonah together are during the wasteful clothing protest in 315. The clips of Andi wearing the protective gear and holding a giant hammer are obviously from 314 (which by the way - we aren’t talking about enough. no cops at pride - just andi mack and her sledgehammer) 

The other moments are more generic, I guess, so we can’t know for sure when they are from. Jonah and Amber at Red Rooster. Buffy giving a thumbs up. A cell phone video of CeCe dancing. Cyrus outside (in the park), and Cyrus inside of Andi Shack. Andi bobbing her head, Andi sitting in a school classroom. I guess those moments could fit in just about anywhere. But it would make sense that with so many recognizable moments from 314-316, the rest of the tiny clips would fit in there somewhere too. But I could be wrong.

Beyond that. It’s not the bench scene. We know the bench scene is in the finale in the Mack backyard. People are really determined to find some alternate theory involving the bench scene instead of just accepting what we already know about it for some reason. The moment where Cyrus is wearing a blue shirt in what appears to be the park is likely whatever Tyrus related scene we get in the b-plot of 315, but it most likely does not involve a bench - and even if it for some reason did, it most likely would not be the bench scene.

summary: To elaborate: a Tyrus SKAM/Elu AU
body:
To elaborate: a Tyrus SKAM/Elu AU

TJ is Lucas, with his best friends Marty (Basile), Reed (Yann), and Lester (Arthur) are juniors at Jefferson highschool.

After being conned into joining a student project by Andi (Imane) for her friend Buffy (Daphné), TJ meets Cyrus (Eliott)—a new transfer student who catches his eye at once—but his attempts to talk to the new boy are initially thwarted by Kira (Chloé), the girl he had kissed at a party the prior weekend before realizing with immense disappointment that he just wasn’t that into it.

Outside of school, issues with his parents have led to TJ living with the old roommates of his traveling older friend, Amber (Manon): Jonah (Mika), a very proud and very weird bisexual, and Gus (Lisa), his ???friend???

TJ quickly becomes infatuated with Cyrus, and ends up spending a night ditching his friends to hang out with him. Cyrus is shy and reserved one minute, and excitedly ranting about his passion project—a short film he’s trying to get funded—the next, and TJ finds it enchanting.

Unfortunately, as he’s leaving, TJ sees Cyrus greet his girlfriend, Iris (Lucille). Hurt, but not wanting to admit to himself the reason, TJ turns to Kira and begins dating her.

But he just can’t seem to keep his eyes off Cyrus…
